Novel begins with Dr. Mortimer approaching Holmes for help in solving the mystery of the supernatural hound that is believed to be responsible for the deaths of several Baskerville family members. Sir Henry Baskerville, the latest heir to the family estate, arrives in London and seeks Holmes' assistance after receiving a mysterious warning. Holmes sends Dr. Watson with Sir Henry to Baskerville Hall to investigate.
As the story unfolds, Holmes continues his investigation in London, while Watson and Sir Henry venture to the eerie moors of Devon. There, they encounter strange occurrences and suspicious characters. The tension between scientific reasoning and supernatural beliefs becomes more pronounced. Eventually, Holmes rejoins them, and together they uncover the truth behind the legend of the hound, revealing a complex plot of murder and intrigue.
